\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
18:30\line }{\cs16\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Kune Collaborative Software}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
\line }{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Samer Hassan, Vicente Ruiz Jurado\line }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://kune.ourproject.org/" }\cs17\i\ai{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\alang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
kune.ourproject.org}}}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Kune is a free/open source distributed social network focused on collaboration rather than just on communication. That is, it focuses on online real-time collaborative editing, decentralized social networking and web publishing, while focusing on workgroups rather than just on individuals. It aims to allow for the creation of online spaces for collaborative work where organizations and individuals can build projects online, coordinate common agendas, set up virtual meetings, publish on the web, and join organizations with similar interests. It has a special focus on Free Culture and social movements needs. }
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
18:40\line }{\cs16\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Shareable Tools}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
\line }{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Tom Lechner\line }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://tomlechner.com/" }\cs17\i\ai{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\alang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
tomlechner.com}}}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
This talk will explore the concept of canvas tool sharing. \line What if we could share the interfaces of tools across applications, and perhaps leverage easy scripting platforms like Processing or paper.js to prototype tools, then easily (tm) transplant to other platforms like Gimp or Inkscape. Artists and designers could then fill their tool belt with their favorite tools, and hack together custom ones as necessary, \line Since Inkscape, Gimp, and others have very different internals, the problem is figuring out enough in common that could be shared, minimizing the coding needed to connect visual interfaces for humans to internal object structure and rendering.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
18:50\line }{\cs16\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
