\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
19:00\line }{\cs16\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Making pages turn: The physical side of F/LOSS design}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
\line }{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Libre Graphics magazine editorial team, Ana Isabel Carvalho, ginger coons, Ricardo Lafuente\line }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://libregraphicsmag.com/" }\cs17\i\ai{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\alang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
libregraphicsmag.com}}}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
For nearly three years, Libre Graphics magazine has existed with the explicit intent of producing a print magazine. In this presentation, we explore the issues and opportunities of physical F/LOSS production. From funding, to raw materials, we discuss the process of attempting to decentralize an object. \line Libre Graphics magazine (ISSN 1925-1416) is a print publication devoted to showcasing and promoting work created with Free/Libre Open Source Software. Since 2010, we have been publishing work about or including artistic practices which integrate Free, Libre and Open software, standards, culture, methods and licenses.}
