Interactivos?'13 is a two week prototyping workshop that will start right after LGM. It will be an unique opportunity for software developers, artists and designers from all over the world to exchange, discuss, produce and imagine Free, Libre and Open source tools for graphics and design. This edition focuses on (re)inventing a Libre Graphics workflow that supports collaboration and exchange.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
10:20\line }{\cs16\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Free Freedom of Speech Kit (F2SK)}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
\line }{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Jos\u233\'e9 Mar\u237\'eda Blanco, Jos\u233\'e9 Mar\u237\'eda Blanco, Mar\u237\'eda Sol\u233\'e9 Bravo, Anna Carreras}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
A portable digital device to show text messages (or even images) in the public space. Developed open free hardware and software, it should be energetically autonomous, light and easy to build. Simplifying the concept it can be thought as a DIY digital banner for demonstrations. \line Therefore our proposal comprises the design, development, production and creation of the Free Freedom of Speech Kit to get a real device and an appropriate open, free SDK control that allows any citizen to display their opinions in real time, to use it as a social or even artistic creation tool.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
10:40\line }{\cs16\b\ab\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Design with Git}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
\line }{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Julien Deswaef\line }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://w.xuv.be/projects/design_with_git" }\cs17\i\ai{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\alang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
w.xuv.be/projects/design_with_git}}}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
As a designer, we usually think in visual terms. Let's see how we could emulate the benefits of distributed source code in the rich colors of a designer's world. \line Git is a distributed version control system now wildly used in the free software world to collaborate and keep track of source code. Since designers today use more and more code to create their work, they naturally turn to Git as a tool to manage their work in progress. The aim of the project is to work on how Git can be integrated more into a graphical designers workflow and create tools that would give a visual feedback of the design changes and collaborations on a specific project.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
