\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Unified Typeface Design is a proposal for the standardization of typeface design in an open source context. It also aims for the promotion of open source typography by introducing a transversal and flexible classification. Technically, UTD is a folder architecture to organize font sources, inspirations and references. It is also a JSON file containing useful meta informations about the typeface and its repository. \line Rapha\u235\'ebl Bastide, graphic designer, hacker, open source evangelist, was born in 1985 in Montpellier, France. He currently lives in Paris and works as a freelance graphic designer and artist.}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
