karl-tux-stadt.de/ktuxs/}}}
\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
In 2001 a professor came up with a new license system for creative work, Creative Commons. In 2004 the first movie under this license system was published. The newspaper called it an "Open Source Movie" but is it a such one? What is an open source movie, is there a definition for them? What is the status of open source movies, do they have a chance? What are the problems of movie makers with open licenses? How to do business with open movies? Are there enough open source tools or the right one to produce open source movies? \line The talk will give an overview on the open movie scene and try to give to all this questions an answer. \line Sirko is since more then 15 years heavily involved into the floss community, he works and worked on different projects. Was long time chief of program at RadioTux, works for different floss events as graphic designer, propagates the use of free software in talks and workshops. Wrote a Inkscape book and a lot of things more.}
