\par \pard\plain \s19\sb0\sa120{\cs17\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Snijlab, WORM and Stadslab Rotterdam are working on a small, transportable and payable Lasercutter. There are already cheap China made lasercutters, and we have a few opensource projects (Buildlog, Lasersaur). But building your own Lasercutter is still a bridge to far for many people. There is little support, no clear information about hardware dealers and all information is to be found on different fora. \line The Mobile Opensource Lasercutter project (for short: MOL) will take the Buildlog project a step further providing a few hardware improvements, clear and comprehensible documentation and will be more easy to use for less technical people.}
